	  </figure></para><exercise id="secfhsst_id195"><title> The Doppler Effect for Sound </title>
      <problem id="probfhsst_id196">
      <para id="id232057">The siren of an ambulance has a frequency of 700 Hz. You are standing on the pavement. If the ambulance drives past you at a speed of 20 m<m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mo>·</m:mo></m:math>s<m:math overflow="scroll"><m:msup><m:mrow/><m:mrow><m:mo>-</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msup></m:math>, what frequency will you hear, when</para>
      <list id="id232087" display="block" list-type="enumerated"><item id="uid5">the ambulance is approaching you
</item>
        <item id="uid6">the ambulance is driving away from you
</item>
      </list>
      <para id="id232118">Take the speed of sound to be 340 m<m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mo>·</m:mo></m:math>s<m:math overflow="scroll"><m:msup><m:mrow/><m:mrow><m:mo>-</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msup></m:math>.
 </para>
      </problem>
